flowRoot.flowPara: Each cluster directory hosts a set of resources created on the
The "sync.yaml" manifest points Flux to the directory hosting the resources to be applied remotely, i.e. on the workload cluster.
This cluster is in the "dev" workspace so consumes the workspace's associated directory.
Each workspace points to a set of "common" resources used to deploy Gatekeeper and other foundational components on workload clusters, e.g. to enforce ServiceAccount usage.
The "sync" manifests point Flux to the workspace-specific Git repository that can be accessed by users on the workload cluster to deploy workloads.
